## Configuration

Environment variables are declared in `edgezero.toml`. Set `API_BASE_URL` to the upstream origin you want `/proxy/...` to target. Adapter-specific secrets are opt-in: uncomment the `#[secret]` field in `crates/{{proj_core}}/src/config.rs` and the matching `[stores.secrets]` block in `edgezero.toml`, then provide the secret value through the wired backend (Cloudflare Worker secret, Fastly Secret Store, Spin secret variable, ...).

### Typed app config (`{{name}}.toml`)

`{{name}}.toml` maps onto `{{NameUpperCamel}}Config` in
`crates/{{proj_core}}/src/config.rs`. Handlers receive it via the
`AppConfig<{{NameUpperCamel}}Config>` extractor -- no manual config-store
or secret-store calls needed. The `{{proj_cli}}` binary wires the typed
push and validate commands:

```sh
# Validate the manifest + typed config (skips secret-field rules at
# push time; runtime validates the resolved secret values per spec 3.3.8):
cargo run -p {{proj_cli}} -- config validate

# Push `{{name}}.toml` as a single blob envelope into the adapter's
# config store. The blob carries every field verbatim -- including
# `#[secret]` fields, whose value at rest is the key NAME (Model A
# per spec 3.3); the runtime extractor swaps each name for the
# resolved secret value at request time.
cargo run -p {{proj_cli}} -- config push --adapter <axum|cloudflare|fastly|spin>

# Compare the local TOML against the deployed remote. `--exit-code`
# turns it into a CI gate: exit 1 if changes exist.
cargo run -p {{proj_cli}} -- config diff --adapter <name> --format json --exit-code
```

Uncomment `[stores.config]` in `edgezero.toml` (and the matching
adapter binding in the per-adapter manifest) before running `config push`.

Use `--key <name>` for per-environment overrides (staging / canary):
the same `{{name}}.toml` can land under multiple keys, and the runtime
picks one via `EDGEZERO__STORES__CONFIG__APP_CONFIG__KEY=<name>`.
Where you set that override depends on the adapter -- Axum reads it
from process env, Cloudflare from worker vars, Spin from application
variables, and Fastly from a dedicated `edgezero_runtime_env` Config
Store that `edgezero provision --adapter fastly` creates. See the
[blob app-config migration guide](https://stackpop.github.io/edgezero/guide/blob-app-config-migration)
for the per-adapter steps and the full operator runbook.
